# Runtime governance artifacts
artifacts/runtime/
artifacts/session/
artifacts/*.db
artifacts/external-project-facts/
# CE-1C.4: timestamp-shaped raw claim-enforcement session packets are runtime-facing,
# not repo-facing tracked evidence. UUID-shaped dirs excluded (design risk — see CE-1D).
# checker-tests/ and claim-enforcement-receipts.ndjson are NOT covered by this pattern.
artifacts/claim-enforcement/session-*/
artifacts/reviewer-handoff/
artifacts/session-summary.txt
artifacts/governance/version_compatibility.json
# Option B (2026-06-17, owner-ratified): these two runtime ledgers are ignored as
# runtime artifacts; durable audit evidence lives in committed memory/ + a
# milestone export path (designed separately). Supersedes the CE-1C.4 note above
# that kept claim-enforcement-receipts.ndjson tracked.
artifacts/claim-enforcement/claim-enforcement-receipts.ndjson
artifacts/session-index.ndjson
# Hygiene defense (2026-06-23): governance runtime writers default --project-root
# to cwd (manage_agent_closeout.py:979 / session_end_hook.py:2245 /
# session_closeout_entry.py:338), so a closeout fired from a sub-directory drops
# an artifacts/ tree there. The patterns above are root-anchored and miss nested
# copies. These any-depth patterns stop a stray nested artifacts/ being committed.
# THIS IS A HYGIENE DEFENSE ONLY, NOT THE ROOT-CAUSE FIX. See
# docs/governance/artifact-write-boundary-2026-06-23.md.
**/artifacts/runtime/
**/artifacts/session/
**/artifacts/claim-enforcement/
**/artifacts/governance/
**/artifacts/*.db
**/artifacts/session-index.ndjson
memory/candidates/*.json
.governance-audit/
# .governance-state.yaml is a regenerated, machine-specific bootstrap snapshot
# (self-labeled "derived context snapshot (session bootstrap only); NOT authority;
# DO NOT edit manually; update PLAN.md"). Regenerable via state_generator.py and
# readers tolerate its absence, so it is untracked to stop perpetual
# timestamp/project_root churn.
.governance-state.yaml

# Nested repo clone (accidental copy of workspace root)
ai-governance-framework/

# Obsidian: read-only reviewer/navigation layer only (derived view, NOT
# authority, NOT a memory writer). Local vault config is never committed.
.obsidian/

